WhiteFox::

She decided it was nothing and came out of hiding.  She causiosly 
started to move through the forest and made her way inland. 

A few hours later, she came to a mountain range. The Sierras.
She made her way through a rouhg maountain pass and started to cross 
the range. She stopped about half way through to make camp and catch 
her breath. 
"If any maximals are here, they have to be here somewhere. I just 
wish I knew where to look. I can't send out a beacon just in case 
there are hostile bots."  she sighed and looked at her 
campfire. "Wel, perhaps I'll get lucky,by the grace of the matrix, 
and find a friend around here." 
Tire and exhausted, she curled up near the fire and fell asleep.
